Approach (Phase 2)

Fatality indicators are further validated by aligning the fatality_indicator field with the confirmed outcome field did_the_child_die? to ensure consistency across the dataset.

An indication of a Fatality = “Yes” or “No” is only retained if it is consistent with the did_the_child_die? field based on the logic below:



---

Logic for Phase 2 Data Alignment

If the fatality_indicator value differs from did_the_child_die?, the record is evaluated.

The update is applied only when:

fatality_indicator contains a valid value: “Y”, “N”, or “U”, and

did_the_child_die? contains a valid value: “Y” or “N”


If both conditions are met:

The value of fatality_indicator is updated to match the value in did_the_child_die?


If the values already match:

No change is made.


If either field contains invalid or missing values:

The record is left unchanged.




---

Key Notes

The did_the_child_die? field is treated as the authoritative source for fatality confirmation.

“Unknown” (“U”) values in fatality_indicator are resolved when a confirmed value (“Y” or “N”) is available.

This process ensures data consistency and accuracy for downstream reporting and analysis.



